            {
              "id": "2e4a519a-8118-31d1-aace-e3fb22ddc603",
              "name": "\"Potential DOM XSS Vulnerability from Assigning User-Controlled Data to innerHTML\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nA potential DOM XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) vulnerability can occur when user-controlled data is assigned to `innerHTML` in JavaScript. This is because `innerHTML` interprets any HTML that it is given, which includes potentially malicious scripts. If an attacker can control the input that is assigned to `innerHTML`, they can inject a script that will be executed by the browser.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the user's email is directly assigned to `innerHTML`. If the email is not properly sanitized and contains a script, it will be executed when the email is displayed.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid using `innerHTML` with user-controlled data. Instead, use `textContent` or `innerText`, which do not interpret HTML and therefore prevent script execution. \n\nIf you must use `innerHTML`, ensure that the user-controlled data is properly sanitized before it is assigned. This can be done by escaping special characters, using a library that provides HTML sanitization, or using a Content Security Policy to restrict what scripts can be executed.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace the vulnerable line of code with:\n\n```javascript\nc_email.textContent = users[i].email;\n```\n\nThis code will display the user's email without interpreting any HTML it may contain.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not appear to have any library dependencies.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [DOM Based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
