            {
              "id": "bb67020f-fbd7-3374-a825-f2e1db570826",
              "name": "\"Potential DOM XSS Vulnerability from Assigning User-Controlled Data to innerHTML\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nA potential DOM XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) vulnerability can occur when user-controlled data is assigned to `innerHTML` in JavaScript. This is because `innerHTML` interprets any HTML that it is given, which includes potentially malicious scripts. If an attacker can control the input that is assigned to `innerHTML`, they can inject a script that will be executed by the browser.\n\nIn the provided code example, `users[i].name` is assigned to `c_name.innerHTML`. If `users[i].name` is user-controlled and not properly sanitized, this could lead to a DOM XSS vulnerability.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid assigning user-controlled data to `innerHTML`. Instead, consider using `textContent` or `innerText`, which do not interpret HTML and therefore are not vulnerable to script injection.\n\nIf you must use `innerHTML`, ensure that the user-controlled data is properly sanitized before it is assigned. This can be done by using a library that provides HTML sanitization functions, or by implementing your own sanitization function that removes or escapes any potentially dangerous characters or sequences.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a fixed version of the provided code example:\n\n```javascript\nc_name.textContent = users[i].name;\n```\n\nIn this version, `textContent` is used instead of `innerHTML`, so any HTML in `users[i].name` will be treated as plain text and not interpreted by the browser.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code example does not appear to have any library dependencies.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [DOM Based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-79"
                ]
              }
