            {
              "id": "c19db147-b975-32c4-8756-28106ee3991d",
              "name": "\"POST Route Auth Middleware Lacks CSRF Protection Vulnerability\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"POST Route Auth Middleware Lacks CSRF Protection Vulnerability\" is a security flaw in JavaScript applications, particularly those using Express.js and middleware for authentication. This vulnerability arises when Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) protection is not implemented in the POST route authentication middleware. CSRF is an attack that tricks the victim into submitting a malicious request. It uses the identity and privileges of the victim to perform an undesired function on their behalf.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the POST route '/useredit' uses an authentication middleware `authHandler.isAuthenticated` but lacks CSRF protection. This means an attacker could potentially forge a request to this endpoint and perform actions as an authenticated user.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should implement CSRF protection in your Express.js application. This can be achieved by using middleware such as `csurf` that provides CSRF protection. \n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nFirst, install the `csurf` middleware:\n\n```bash\nnpm install csurf\n```\n\nThen, include it in your application and use it in your routes:\n\n```javascript\nvar csrf = require('csurf');\nvar csrfProtection = csrf({ cookie: true });\n\nrouter.post('/useredit', csrfProtection, authHandler.isAuthenticated, appHandler.userEditSubmit);\n```\n\nIn this updated code, `csrfProtection` middleware is added to the '/useredit' POST route. This middleware will validate the CSRF token in the request, providing protection against CSRF attacks.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- Express.js: A web application framework for Node.js.\n- csurf: CSRF protection middleware for Express.js.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP CSRF Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross-Site_Request_Forgery_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-352: Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/352.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-352",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/352.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-352"
                ]
              }
            },
