            {
              "id": "f515b20b-35a1-3eca-92a1-5a132b0ced80",
              "name": "\"Mathjs.eval Request Data Vulnerability\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe `mathjs.eval` function in the Math.js library is a powerful tool that can evaluate mathematical expressions. However, it can also be a potential security vulnerability if not used properly. If user input is passed directly into the `mathjs.eval` function without proper sanitization, it can lead to Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerabilities. This is because `mathjs.eval` can evaluate not only mathematical expressions, but also JavaScript code. An attacker could potentially send a malicious request that includes JavaScript code, which would then be executed on the server.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should never directly pass user input into the `mathjs.eval` function. Instead, you should sanitize and validate the user input before using it. You can use the `mathjs.parse` and `mathjs.compile` functions to safely parse and evaluate mathematical expressions without the risk of code execution.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is an example of how you can safely use `mathjs.eval` with user input:\n\n```javascript\nconst mathjs = require('mathjs');\nconst express = require('express');\nconst bodyParser = require('body-parser');\n\nconst app = express();\napp.use(bodyParser.json());\n\napp.post('/calculate', (req, res) => {\n  const eqn = req.body.eqn;\n  const sanitizedEqn = mathjs.parse(eqn).compile().evaluate();\n  res.send({ result: sanitizedEqn });\n});\n\napp.listen(3000, () => console.log('Server running on port 3000'));\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\n- mathjs\n- express\n- body-parser\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A1 Injection](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A1_2017-Injection)\n- [CWE-94: Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/94.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-95",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/95.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
