            {
              "id": "f5f2ad76-f1a4-300a-8024-a03f01c1b1e6",
              "name": "Detected Unescaped EJS Output Vulnerability Allowing XSS Attacks",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Detected Unescaped EJS Output Vulnerability Allowing XSS Attacks\" is a vulnerability that occurs when user input is not properly sanitized or escaped before being rendered on a webpage. This can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks, where an attacker can inject malicious scripts into webpages viewed by other users. In the context of EJS (Embedded JavaScript) templates, this vulnerability can occur when the `<%- %>` syntax is used, which does not escape HTML characters.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, always escape user input that is being rendered on a webpage. In EJS, you can use the `<%= %>` syntax to automatically escape HTML characters. This will prevent any HTML tags in the user input from being interpreted as actual HTML, thus preventing XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace the `<%- %>` syntax with `<%= %>`. Here's how you can fix the provided code:\n\n```javascript\n<td><%= output.products[i].code %></td>\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- EJS: A JavaScript templating engine used to generate HTML markup with plain JavaScript.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
